<p>
  Need to turn a block of text into a PDF file? Whether it's notes, a draft, plain text from a database, or content from a .txt file, converting text to PDF is a common task. The good news: you do not need to install any software or create an account to do it. This guide shows you the fastest free methods.
</p>

<h2>The Fastest Method: Free Browser-Based Text to PDF</h2>

<p>
  The quickest way to convert text to PDF is using a free online tool that works entirely in your browser. <a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf">PDFWonder's Text to PDF converter</a> requires no signup, processes everything locally (your text is never uploaded), and generates the PDF in seconds.
</p>

<ol>
  <li>Go to the <a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf">Text to PDF Converter</a>.</li>
  <li>Type or paste your text into the input area.</li>
  <li>Choose your page size (A4 or US Letter), font size, and margins.</li>
  <li>Click <strong>Generate PDF</strong>.</li>
  <li>Your PDF downloads directly to your device.</li>
</ol>

<a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf" class="tool-cta">
  <div class="cta-label">Free Tool — No Signup</div>
  <div class="cta-title">Text to PDF Converter — Convert Instantly →</div>
  <div class="cta-desc">Paste any text and download a PDF in seconds. No upload, no account, 100% browser-based. Your text never leaves your device.</div>
