<h2>How to Convert a .txt File to PDF</h2>

<p>
  Have a .txt file you want to convert? Here is the simplest process:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open your .txt file in Notepad (Windows) or TextEdit (Mac).</li>
  <li>Press <strong>Ctrl+A</strong> (Windows) or <strong>Cmd+A</strong> (Mac) to select all text.</li>
  <li>Press <strong>Ctrl+C</strong> / <strong>Cmd+C</strong> to copy.</li>
  <li>Paste into the <a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf">Text to PDF tool</a>.</li>
  <li>Click Generate PDF and download.</li>
</ol>

<h2>How to Convert Text to PDF Using Microsoft Word</h2>

<p>
  If you have Word installed and need more formatting control:
</p>
<ol>
  <li>Open Microsoft Word and paste or type your text.</li>
  <li>Format it as needed (font, headings, spacing).</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>File → Save As → PDF</strong> or <strong>File → Export → Create PDF/XPS</strong>.</li>
  <li>Choose your save location and click <strong>Publish</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<p>
  This method is best when you need rich formatting — but it requires Word to be installed and does not work without the software.
</p>

<h2>How to Convert Text to PDF Using Google Docs</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open <a href="https://docs.google.com" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Google Docs</a> in your browser.</li>
  <li>Create a new document and paste your text.</li>
  <li>Go to <strong>File → Download → PDF Document (.pdf)</strong>.</li>
  <li>The PDF saves to your downloads folder.</li>
</ol>
<p>
  Google Docs is free and works in any browser but requires a Google account. For plain text without formatting, the browser tool above is faster.
</p>

<h2>How to Convert Text to PDF on iPhone</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open Safari and go to <a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf">PDFWonder Text to PDF</a>.</li>
  <li>Paste your text into the tool.</li>
  <li>Tap Generate PDF — the file downloads to your Files app.</li>
</ol>
<p>
  Alternatively, on iPhone you can use the built-in print-to-PDF feature: open any app with your text, tap Share → Print, then pinch outward on the preview to save as PDF.
</p>

<h2>How to Convert Text to PDF on Android</h2>

<ol>
  <li>Open Chrome and go to <a href="/pdfwonder/text-to-pdf">PDFWonder Text to PDF</a>.</li>
  <li>Paste your text and tap Generate PDF.</li>
  <li>The file saves to your Downloads folder.</li>
</ol>

<h2>When to Use Text to PDF vs Other PDF Tools</h2>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Text to PDF:</strong> Best for plain text, notes, drafts, and .txt file content</li>
  <li><strong>Word / Docs to PDF:</strong> Best when you need formatted documents with headings, tables, and images</li>
  <li><strong><a href="/pdfwonder/pdf-merger">PDF Merger</a>:</strong> When you need to combine existing PDFs</li>
  <li><strong><a href="/pdfwonder/pdf-to-text">PDF to Text</a>:</strong> The reverse — extract text from an existing PDF</li>
</ul>

